## Melt 3: Context Engineering as Practice, Void Management as Theory

### The Practice: Context Engineering (Karpathy 2025)

Context engineering is what practitioners DO:
- Curate system prompts
- Structure few-shot examples
- Manage conversation history
- Integrate external tools (MCP)
- Compress and summarize context

These are ACTIVITIES without theoretical grounding.

### The Theory: Void Management (This Thesis)

Void management explains WHY the activities work:

| Practice | Theory |
|----------|--------|
| Curate system prompts | Define void dimensions |
| Structure few-shot examples | Provide instantiation templates |
| Manage conversation history | Prevent scene accumulation |
| Integrate external tools | Enable void-to-void composition |
| Compress and summarize | Convert scene to void |

### The Contribution Statement

> Context engineering is the emerging practice of LLM context curation. 
> Void management is the theoretical framework that explains its mechanisms. 
> Without the theory, practice is ad-hoc and unreliable. 
> Without the practice, theory is untested speculation. 
> This thesis provides the theory; 150+ hours of practice provides the evidence.
</melt>

